<P>
   &UR; NATO'S BLUNDER MAY HARM HUMAN RIGHTS BEYOND KOSOVO &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Editorial) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By THE EDITORIAL BOARD OF THE INDEPENDENT, LONDON &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In any war, the wrong targets are going to be hit and civilians
are going to be killed, but in this war the misjudgments and
mistakes just keep coming.
</P>
<P>
   ``If there is one building in Belgrade we would like not to have
hit, it was the Chinese embassy,'' a Foreign Office official
admitted on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   This was NATO's biggest blunder yet, because it threatens the
diplomatic house of cards so carefully constructed over the past
week... &LR;  &QL;
</P>
