   ROSEMARY-BUSH (Undated) _ I get a bad case of rosemary
chauvinism in the spring. My motivation couldn't be culinary; I
pinch little sprigs my own rosemary bush all year round and,
traditionally, rosemary is teamed with fall and wintery dishes.
Still, when I cart new basil and chervil, oregano, parsley and
thyme onto the terrace every spring, I fuss with them briefly and
then dote on my rosemary. Next to the fragile baby annuals, the
perennial rosemary is so valiant, thriving in the perpetual fumes
of trucks and cars and forgiving my erratic attentions. By Molly
