<HEADLINE>
HIGH SCHOOL SETS RECORDS WITH 57-0 WIN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ If only Pilgrim High could have gotten out
Christian Hariot and Julio Bautista in Tuesday's Heritage League
baseball game, the Patriots could have held visiting Faith Baptist
to 35 hits and who knows how many fewer runs.
</P>
<P>
   But Hariot was unstoppable (9 for 9 with four home runs and 12
RBI) and Bautista almost as tough an out (6 for 8 with four doubles
and 13 RBI), and Faith Baptist wound up setting or tying at least
five Southern Section records in a 57-0 five-inning mercy-rule win.
</P>
<P>
   The Contenders (15-5, 10-1) established single-game marks for
runs (breaking a 77-year-old record), hits (50) and tied records
for team home runs (nine), individual homers (four by Hariot) and
doubles (four by Bautista, who raised his area-leading average to
.686.
</P>
</TEXT>
