r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-COWBOYS-MILLS-TEX     05-12 0365
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-MILLS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS KEEP MILLS WITH THREE-YEAR DEAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The Cowboys reached an agreement with free-agent
wide receiver Ernie Mills yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   The three-year deal is worth $2.275 million, including a
$375,000 signing bonus, said a source who spoke on condition of
anonymity. Under terms of the deal, Mills would get a $400,000 base
salary in 1999, a $300,000 roster bonus in June of 2000, a $400,000
base in 2000 and an $800,000 base in 2001, the source said.
</P>
<P>
   The last year of the contract is voidable.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he's happy in Dallas and wanted to stay there,'' said
Mills' agent, Doug Wright.
</P>
<P>
   Mills, who is entering his ninth NFL season, caught 28 passes
for 479 yards and four touchdowns last season. He suffered a
lacerated small intestine Nov. 22 against Seattle and missed the
final five regular-season games.
</P>
<P>
   He is expected to be the Cowboys' third receiver in 1999 behind
Michael Irvin and Raghib Ismail.
LaFleur fractures ankle
</P>
<P>
   Starting tight end David LaFleur fractured his right ankle in a
morning workout yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys officials, however, said they are confident LaFleur will
be back in time for the start of training camp July 26. He is
expected to be in a cast three weeks.
</P>
<P>
   LaFleur, a third-year veteran, missed the final three games last
season with a sprained right knee.
Davis banned
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver Billy Davis' absence from the Cowboys'
twice-a-week workouts is quite telling about his future. Davis, who
is under contract, was told his presence at the workouts wasn't
necessary and was banned from using the Cowboys' facilities for
personal workouts, said a source close to the situation.
</P>
<P>
   Davis' name no longer adorns a locker in the team locker room.
He is expected to be released, but the Cowboys benefit under the
salary cap if they wait until June 1.
Briefly
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys signed rookie cornerback Kevin Brooks from the
University of South Carolina to a free-agent contract.
</P>
<P>
   Former Cowboys guard Nate Newton visited the Oakland Raiders
last week as his search for a new team continues.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-12-99 0817EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
