<SLUG> BC-NYTBOOK-CONTENTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
 
 (Editors: Following is a list of slugs and titles of the books
reviewed in the New York Times Book Review for Sunday May 16, 1999.
<TEXT>
<P>
   ----------------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   ON THE COVER
</P>
<P>
   ----------------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-NYTSF, ANOTHER WORLD By Pat Barker. 278 pp. New York:
Farrar, Straus &AMP; Giroux. $24. Pat Barker's novel about a family
struggling to survive in northern England recalls memories of the
Great War.
</P>
<P>
   INTERVIEW-NYTSF, INTERVIEW WITH PAT BARKER, OLD WAR WOUNDS by
Alida Becker
</P>
<P>
   --------------------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   FICTION
</P>
<P>
   --------------------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-CENTURY-NYTSF, TURN OF THE CENTURY By Kurt Andersen. 659
pp. New York: Random House. $24.95. Kurt Andersen's novel finds the
