<HEADLINE>
LEONARD NIMOY STARS IN ``STAR TREK: INSURRECTION'' 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Resending for all needing.)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Star Trek: Insurrection'' _ Maybe the title is
meant to suggest the feelings expressed by the William
Shatner-Leonard Nimoy crew when confronted with the script of this
``Star Trek'' drek.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yes, UConn!'' _ The official 1999 NCAA basketball championship
video is out, for less than $20. Condensed to 50 minutes, the CBS
Video production includes highlights from the tournament as well as
the thrilling final game against Duke.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   KUBRICK SET: It took a director of Stanley Kubrick's stature to
unite three competing companies _ Warner Home Video, MGM Home
Entertainment, and Columbia TriStar Home Video. On June 29, just
two weeks before Kubrick's final feature, ``Eyes Wide Shut,''
opens, they are releasing ``The Stanley Kubrick Collection'' on
both VHS and DVD. The set includes ``2001: A Space Odyssey,''
``Paths of Glory,'' and ``The Killing'' from MGM; ``Lolita,'' ``A
Clockwork Orange,'' ``Barry Lyndon,'' ``The Shining,'' and ``Full
Metal Jacket'' from Warner; and ``Dr. Strangelove'' from Columbia
Tristar. The set will sell for $124.92 on VHS and $149.92 on DVD.
Individual titles will sell for $19.98 on VHS and $24.98 on DVD
(except for ``Barry Lyndon,'' a double cassette, for $24.98 in
either format).
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 18: ``The Impostors,'' ``Batman Beyond:
The Movie,'' ``Bent,'' ``Holy Man,'' ``In Dreams,'' ``Memorial
Day,'' ``My Sweet Suicide,'' ``Rowing With the Wind,'' ``Shadow of
Doubt.'' May 25: ``Saving Private Ryan,'' ``Gloria,'' ``Alice in
Wonderland,'' ``Horatio Hornblower,'' ``The Aviator's Wife,'' ``The
Marquise of O,'' ``Forbidden Fruit,'' ``Wrestlemania XV,''
``Hellcab.'' June 1: ``Berenstain Bears'' (three new episodes),
``The Base,'' ``Gunshy.'' June 8: ``From the Earth to the Moon,''
``Treehouse Hostage,'' ``Psycho'' (remake), ``Gods and Monsters,''
``Before Stonewall,'' ``After Stonewall,'' ``Last Rites.'' June 15:
``Little Voice,'' ``The World Within,'' ``Enemy of the State,''
``The Faculty,'' ``Facade,'' ``The Patriot.'' June 22: ``Waking Ned
Devine,'' ``Patch Adams,'' ``A Simple Plan,'' ``Rushmore,''
``Wishful Thinking,'' ``Sweethearts,'' ``The Life of Birds,''
``Storm of the Century.''
</P>
