<HEADLINE>
FRAGRANT COOKIES BLEND ORANGE, BASIL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Beverly Bundy Peg Shocklee, Fort Worth, writes looking for the
recipe for the orange basil cookies that are often sold at the Fort
Worth Herb Society's annual sale.
</P>
<P>
   (In case you'd rather buy the cookies, this year's event is
Saturday at the Fort Worth Botanic Garden. Admission is $3, and
there's usually a terrific variety of plants available.)
</P>
<P>
   The Herb Society was nice enough to share its recipe for these
cookies.
</P>
<P>
   ORANGE BASIL COOKIES
</P>
<P>
   Yields 5 dozen
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   1 egg yolk
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon orange juice
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon grated orange peel
</P>
<P>
   18-ounce box yellow cake mix
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon orange extract
</P>
<P>
   1 cup raisins, optional
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped nuts
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons dried basil
</P>
<P>
   Combine butter, cream cheese, egg yolk and juice. Add dry cake
mix and rest of ingredients. Chill dough. Bake on buttered cookie
sheet at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per cookie with raisins: 72 calories, 4
grams fat, 9 grams carbohydrates, 1 gram protein, 10 milligrams
cholesterol, 75 milligrams sodium, 47 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   A sauce for seafood: Anne Semple, Fort Worth, e-mails that she
would like the recipe for the remoulade sauce from City Club. She
sampled the sauce at a Bass Hall event. Here's that recipe,
provided by Richard Schafer, City Club chef.
</P>
<P>
   CITY CLUB'S CAJUN REMOULADE
</P>
<P>
   Yields 1 1/4 cup
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons Zatarain Cajun mustard
</P>
<P>
   1 cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chopped capers
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon chopped parsley
</P>
<P>
   Juice from one lemon
</P>
<P>
   Cayenne pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients and serve as a dipping sauce for shrimp
or any other seafood.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per tablespoon: 73 calories, 8 grams fat, 1
gram carbohydrates, trace protein, 6 milligrams cholesterol, 107
milligrams sodium, 96 percent of calories from fat. Request:
</P>
<P>
   Dorothy M. Overton, Fort Worth, is looking for a recipe she
clipped from the Fort Worth Star-Telegram about 18 years ago. It's
for Cornish game hens with a corn bread/sausage stuffing.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
