<P>
   SCI-DUKE-RESEARCH (Dateline to kum) _ Folo on the suspension of
nearly all government-funded research involving humans at Duke
University Medical Center. By Philip J. Hilts. (1200 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-LIPOSUCTION-RISK (Undated) _ A team of doctors in New York
is questioning the safety of liposuction, the immensely popular
cosmetic surgery in which body fat is vacuumed out through a tube
to get rid of ``thunder thighs,'' ``love handles,'' pot bellies and
other hated bulges. The doctors' warning, being published in the
New England Journal of Medicine, is based on their review of five
deaths that occurred in New York after liposuction from 1993 to
1998. By Denise Grady. (800 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-AGING-GENES (Undated) _ The Discovery of a new gene in the
C. elegans roundworm suggests an interesting link between its
life-lengthening genes and a leading theory of human aging, the
belief that cells age through oxidative stress as reactive
chemicals attack DNA. By Nicholas Wade. (800 words)
</P>
