2 official the Treasury Department. Eizenstat, an undersecretary at
the State Department, grew up in Atlanta, attending Grady High
School. He also headed Atlanta-based Powell and Goldstein's law
offices in Washington. His family is prominent in the Atlanta
Jewish community. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TEACHER-TESTING _ WASHINGTON - Teaching hopefuls who passed
licensing tests to teach courses like English, science, social
studies and math got above-average scores on their SAT and ACT
tests, but teachers of elementary, special and physical education
had lower verbal and math scores on those tests of their academic
ability, says a study to be released Wednesday. Leaders of national
organizations of teacher colleges, teachers and school boards
discuss the significance. (Mollison, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
