Florida. (Developing) (Hiassan, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   RIVER _ The National Park Service, as part of a national policy,
is banning personal water craft from the Chattahoochee River
National Recreation Area. The ban, which goes into effect Friday,
means there will be no riding of Jet Skis and the like on the river
from the dam to Standing Peachtree Creek. But not that many people
were zooming along the river anyway, park officials say, and most
of them limited use to the Bull Sluice Lake area, park officials
say. (Williams, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
