<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-KOSOVO-NATO-NYT, which moved in
``i'' news file.)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``If I'm a young Serb soldier, eating my lunch at 2 o'clock in
the afternoon, and out of the gray skies over my head comes a
hundred plus Mark-82s, that ought to be a signal that we're
entering a new phase of the air campaign and we're taking the
gloves off a little more.''
</P>
<P>
   _LT. GEN. MICHAEL SHORT, NATO's air war commander.
</P>
</TEXT>
