<HEADLINE>
N.Y. TIMES SELECTS CHIEF OF NEWS SERVICES DIVISION 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The appointment of Thomas Carley as president of the
News Services division at The New York Times was announced
Wednesday. He was previously director of business development for
the division.
</P>
<P>
   Carley, who joined the company in 1987 as a circulation
marketing analyst, will help develop and market services outside
the main newspaper that broaden the reach of The Times. He will
oversee The New York Times Syndication Sales Corp., The New York
Times News Service, TimesFax, Rights and Permissions, Photo
Archives, Book Development, Large Type Weekly and Crossword Product
Development.
</P>
<P>
   Carley will report to Joseph Lelyveld, executive editor of The
Times, and to Janet Robinson, president and general manager of the
paper. &QL;
</P>
